{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":195395,"duration_api_ms":229095,"num_turns":26,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"29155c43-f512-4f9e-a800-0e9dfe62897d","total_cost_usd":1.0216362,"usage":{"input_tokens":17,"cache_creation_input_tokens":51229,"cache_read_input_tokens":711034,"output_tokens":3869,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":51229,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":17,"outputTokens":3869,"cacheReadInputTokens":711034,"cacheCreationInputTokens":51229,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.77250825,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":180,"outputTokens":11926,"cacheReadInputTokens":926217,"cacheCreationInputTokens":77357,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.24912795000000004,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Reviewed all changes across the 6 implementation rounds. The diff touches 2 files: `src/contexts/milestone_record/model.rs` and `src/adapters/fs.rs`.\n\n**Issue 1 (Journal detail struct drift):** Fixed correctly. The duplicate `StartJournalDetails` and `CompletionJournalDetails` struct definitions in `fs.rs` are removed; both render and parse paths now use the same canonical structs defined in `model.rs` with `#[serde(deny_unknown_fields)]` and `Deserialize`. Drift is structurally impossible — adding a field to the model struct forces the adapter to handle it since they share the type. Round-trip tests confirm serialization stability.\n\n**Issue 2 (Runless-to-named completion):** Fixed correctly. `update_task_run` at lines 3028-3037 accepts a runless match when `started_at` matches, then backfills `run_id` at line 3213. Mismatched `started_at` is properly rejected (line 3039-3050). Tests cover both the happy path (`runless_start_completed_with_named_run_id`) and the rejection path (`runless_match_rejected_when_started_at_mismatches`), plus conflicting plan_hash rejection (`completion_with_conflicting_plan_hash_rejects_runless_match`).\n\n**Issue 3 (plan_hash auto-population):** Fixed correctly. `record_task_run_start` at lines 2932-2936 reads `snapshot_plan_hash()` when the caller omits `plan_hash`. The helper (lines 2546-2560) properly distinguishes not-found (silent None) from unexpected errors (logs warning). Auto-population is intentionally NOT applied during finalization (comment at lines 3233-3237), which is correct because the plan may have evolved between start and finish. Tests cover auto-population (`plan_hash_auto_populated_from_snapshot`), explicit precedence (`explicit_plan_hash_takes_precedence_over_snapshot`), and plan evolution replay (`terminal_replay_after_plan_evolution_succeeds`).\n\nAll 351 tests pass. The implementation is sound with no bugs found. One minor observation noted as an amendment below.","amendments":[{"body":"The `render_start_journal_details` and `render_completion_journal_details` functions now allocate owned Strings for every field (`.to_owned()`, `.map(str::to_owned)`) on every call, whereas the prior `&'a str` / borrowed payload approach was zero-copy for serialization. This is functionally correct and the allocation cost is negligible for the current usage pattern, but the API could retain a borrowing render path (e.g. a `StartJournalDetails::from_parts` constructor that borrows into a `Cow` or just accepts owned values at the call site) to avoid the regression for any future hot-path usage. This is a low-priority observation, not a blocking issue.","rationale":"Performance regression is negligible now but worth noting since the original code was explicitly designed to avoid allocation. If this render path is ever called in a tight loop (e.g. bulk migration), the extra allocations would add up."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"3bceb602-adbb-467a-8dbc-43ab49b18fa4"}
